# Agents (this repository)

## Read first

**Repository entry:** this file (`.cursor/rules/agents-entry.mdc`) is **always-on** in Cursor. It orients **planes, non‑negotiables, and where procedure lives** — not stem matrices, command catalogs, or feature-specific law (**skills** + **PO** own those).

## Four planes

**PO** — Intent, acceptance, RouteName, non-goals in repo-root **`app/<Subsystem>/<Module>/…`**.

**Portable law** — **`.cursor/skills/core-*`** stems and **`.cursor/skills/app-portable-recipes/`** (checks beside normative prose). Every **`core-*`** folder includes a skill-root **`enforce.sh`** (bundled gates or a norms-only no-op); **`./mono enforce <stem>`** resolves stems to that entry — hub docs (**repository entry**, **`.cursor/skills/README.md`**) do not inventory inner **`*.sh`** drivers. **Driver policy** (fold extra root drivers into **`enforce.sh`** or documented **`enforce-<slug>.sh`**; prefer **`rules/`** over ambiguous skill-root **`check/`**): **refactoring** **`SKILL.md`** § Skill-root **`enforce.sh`**.

**Ops** — **`k8s/`** + **core-ops-k8s**; cluster verify when **`k8s/`** changes.

**Code** — **`servers/*`**, **`clients/*`**. **One product stack per change** unless the brief explicitly splits work.

## Non‑negotiables

- When behavior depends on product intent: attach **this hub** + **linked PO capsule**.
- **No upward Markdown links** from PO, **`k8s/`** operator docs, or generic editor config into portable skill trees — cite **stem ids** / slugs in prose.
- **Agent terminal:** repo-wide **`rg`** (and similar): **explicit path** + **`</dev/null>`** so stdin never blocks.
- Do **not** paste a second portable stem matrix — **`./mono enforce help`** and stem folders own runnable truth.

